race.comment: Former NSW galloper KARMARDO (1) is unlucky to still be a maiden placing in four of six overall and should find this assignment easier than what he was facing down south. Gets plenty of weight relief with the 3kg claim and looks the one they all have to run down. LORD VALEN (2) has placed three of four over this six-furlong journey and will be ready to peak now third-up from the spell. Looms as the main danger. MAVEN (3) resumes here but the form he showed when last in work was good enough for a race of this calibre. Respect with Wiggins on board. OSCAR BOOIE (6) has been in the betting at the past three outings and where there's smoke there's fire. Keep safe. REDLIGHTS ON (7) next in line from the inside alley.
